# .gitignore — aero-fighters-v2
# Release: aero-fighters-v2-photorealistic-inhauma-v1
# Canonical Epic UE5 ignore list, extended for this project's tooling.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# UE5 build artifacts
# These are regenerated from source by UnrealBuildTool; committing them
# bloats the repo and causes merge conflicts.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Binaries/
DerivedDataCache/
Intermediate/
Saved/
Build/
*.VC.db
*.opensdf
*.opendb
*.sdf
*.sln
*.suo
*.xcodeproj/
*.xcworkspace/

# Compiled output symbols/imports (Windows link artifacts)
*.target
*.exp
*.ilk
*.lib
*.pdb

# Temporary asset files created by UE5 during cook/save
*.uasset.tmp

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local environment + offline tile cache (SPEC §8, NFR-V2-02, RR-V2-07)
# .env.local is operator-created from .env.local.example — never commit it.
# *-tile-cache/ directories contain gigabytes of Google tile data that must
# not be committed (Google ToS, repo size).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.env.local
*-tile-cache/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS / editor noise
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
.vscode/
.idea/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python harness venv + caches (Tools/)
# The venv is operator-local; .pyc files are bytecode caches.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Tools/__pycache__/
Tools/*.pyc
Tools/venv/
Tools/.venv/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# UE5 Staging output (SPEC §11)
# Shipping builds land in Saved/StagedBuilds/. Saved/ is already ignored
# above, but the explicit entry documents the intent. Operators pull builds
# out of StagedBuilds/ manually; git does not track them.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
StagedBuilds/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reports + closure artifacts
# git LFS tracks keeper baseline screenshots (Reports/baselines/**).
# One-shot timestamped run reports are ignored to avoid polluting history.
# The pattern matches YYYY or 2026 in the filename suffix.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Reports/perf-*.html
Reports/screenshot-diff-*.html
Reports/smoke/*-2026*.md
